Description . Male ( Holotype , IBSP 21446 ) Carapace orange with brown pattern as shown on
Fig. 68
. Chelicerae orange with median longitudinal stripe. Pedipalps orange with dorsal and prolateral brown longitudinal stripes. Labium orange with pale brown base. Endites pale yellow. Sternum orange with brown markings in front of each coxae, extending towards the center. Legs orange. Femora and tibiae I–IV with pair of parallel ventral black stripes. Abdomen whitish gray. Anterior half mottled with black spots, posterior half with 3 transversal black stripes (
Fig. 68
). Total length 4.5 . Carapace slightly domed, 2.2 long, 1.9 wide. Eye diameters: PME 0.18 , ALE 0.16 , PLE 0.16 . Lateral eyes on a tubercle. Chelicerae with subapical hyaline keel and inconspicuous stridulatory ridges. Labium 0.16 long, 0.26 wide. Sternum 1.18 long, 0.96 wide. Leg measurements: I: femur 5.0, patella 0.6 , tibia 4.6 , metatarsus 6.1 , tarsus 0.7 , total 17.0; II: 3.4 , 0.6 , 3.5 , 3.9 , 0.6 , 12.0; III: 2.1 , 0.5 , 1.9 , 2.2 , 0.6 , 7.3 ; IV: 3.1 , 0.6 , 2.8 , 3.2 , 0.7 , 10.4 . Palpal femur with long, slender stridulatory pick with rounded and projected socket. Cymbium with single strong distal spine (
Fig. 69
). Bulb 0.60 long, medially constricted and bent. Distal region blunt and bifid, prolaterally with small triangular hyaline lamina (
Fig. 69
) and retrolaterally with large and strong retrolateral curved prong (
Fig. 70–71
). Abdomen 2.3 long, 1.8 wide, covered with slender hairs.

Female ( Paratype , IBSP 22027 ) Coloration pattern as in male. Total length 6.0. Carapace domed, 2.8 long, 2.4 wide. Eye diameters: PME 0.14 , ALE 0.16 , PLE 0.14 . Lateral eyes on a tubercle. Chelicerae as in male. Labium 0.22 long, 0.34 wide. Sternum 1.3 long, 1.1 wide. Leg measurements: I: femur 3.6 , patella 0.6 , tibia 3.9 , metatarsus 4.8 , tarsus 0.8 , total 13.7 ; II: 2.9 , 0.6 , 2.8 , 3.3 , 0.7 , 10.3 ; III: 1.9 , 0.5 , 1.6 , 2.1 , 0.5 , 6.6 ; IV: 2.7 , 0.6 , 2.4 , 2.9 , 0.7 , 9.3 . Palpal femur as in male. Epigynum with ridged positioning ridges separated from each other by three times their width (
Fig. 72
). Vulva with large hyaline pockets, widely separated and with small, triangular sclerotized areas, adjacent to median membranous area (
Fig. 73
). Abdomen 3.2 long, 2.7 wide, as in male.
